<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Southampton are interested in signing Everton midfielder Tom Davies.  </p>

<p>Saints boss Ralph Hasenhuttl has made no secret of his desire to sign a replacement for Pierre-Emile Hojbjerg, who left to join Tottenham Hotspur over the summer. </p>

<p>Southampton are now set to sign the England under-21 international on a season-long loan deal, according to talkSPORT.</p>

<p>Southampton are set to sign Everton midfielder Tom Davies on a season-long loan deal</p>

<p>The 22-year-old has fallen down the pecking order at Goodison Park following the arrivals of Allan and Abdoulaye Doucoure. </p>

<p>Davies has played 123 times for his boyhood club, including twice this season.</p>

<p>He has netted six goals in that time, including one at St Mary's last season, but has seen midfielders Abdoulaye Doucoure and Allan arrive at Goodison Park this summer</p>

<p>Southampton would like to take the 22-year-old on loan with an option to buy, while Everton would prefer to sell. </p>

<p>Davies has fallen down the pecking order following arrivals of Allan and Abdoulaye Doucoure</p>
